{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase funding for mediation and arbitration in family courts",
        "additional_details": "We believe that the current family court system is slow, costly, and prioritises conflict over children\u2019s interests. Many parents face long delays and limited access to evidence. We believe non-adversarial solutions like mediation and arbitration may help to resolve disputes more effectively, fostering cooperation and preserving family relationships. We believe the Government must ensure a fairer, faster, and more child-focused system that prevents trauma and supports active, shared parenting.",
        "background": "We urge the Government to increase funding for non-adversarial solutions such as mediation and arbitration. We hope that this may result in more transparency, fair processes, and a shift towards shared parenting, ensuring children\u2019s best interests are the primary focus.",
